cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper focuses on extracting features from movie posters using computer vision techniques. 
2. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper aims to estimate the winner of film festivals based on movie posters, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with analyzing movie posters, which is a form of multimedia content. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible sub-category as the paper suggests a possibility of modeling human taste for movie recommendation, which can be seen as an AI application. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also possible as the paper uses various feature types to extract information from movie posters, which can be seen as a machine learning task.
